<article class="itinerary-popup-content">
  <p>
    Explore Poland through four iconic cities on a 6-day journey that blends royal heritage,
    UNESCO landmarks, Baltic charm, and vibrant urban life.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 1: Arrival in Krakow</h3>
  <p>
    Arrival at Krakow airport. Transfer by coach to the hotel, check-in, welcome dinner, and
    overnight stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 2: Krakow Highlights</h3>
  <p>
    Breakfast at the hotel. Guided visit of Krakow's historic center, including Wawel Hill with
    the Royal Castle and Cathedral, the Old Town Market Square, the Cloth Hall, and St. Mary's
    Basilica. Lunch and free time in the afternoon for individual exploration. Dinner and
    overnight stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 3: Transfer to Warsaw and Old Town Orientation</h3>
  <p>
    Breakfast at the hotel. Departure for Warsaw. On arrival, orientation tour of the capital,
    rebuilt after World War II and now one of the country's key cultural hubs. Visit the Old Town
    area around Market Square and admire the Royal Castle exteriors. Dinner and overnight stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 4: Baltic Journey to Gdansk</h3>
  <p>
    Breakfast at the hotel. Continue to Gdansk on the Baltic coast. Guided walk through the main
    highlights of the historic center, known for merchant architecture and maritime history.
    Dinner and overnight stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 5: Transfer to Wroclaw and City Walk</h3>
  <p>
    Breakfast at the hotel. Transfer to Wroclaw, one of Poland's most elegant and lively cities.
    Guided stroll through the Market Square and the old town's most emblematic corners. Dinner
    and overnight stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 6: Departure to Italy</h3>
  <p>
    Breakfast at the hotel. Transfer to the airport for the return flight to Italy.
  </p>
</article>
